1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,530
Invest in idea starters.

2
00:00:02,879 --> 00:00:09,490
Education helps you mold your mind, stretch it, train it to meet new situations and solve problems.

3
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:12,530
Idea starters serve a related purpose.

4
00:00:12,719 --> 00:00:16,929
They feed your mind, give you constructive material to think about.

5
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:20,769
Where are the best sources of idea starters?

6
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:27,250
There are many, but to get a steady supply of high-quality idea material, why not do this?

7
00:00:27,519 --> 00:00:36,210
Resolve to purchase at least one stimulating book each month and subscribe to two magazines or journals that stress ideas.

8
00:00:36,559 --> 00:00:44,050
For only a minor sum and a minimum of time, you can be tuned in to some of the best thinkers available anywhere.

9
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:50,130
At a luncheon one day, I overheard one fellow say, but it costs too much.

10
00:00:50,239 --> 00:00:53,010
I can't afford to take the Wall Street Journal.

11
00:00:53,279 --> 00:01:01,809
His companion, obviously a much more success-minded person, replied, well, I've found that I can't afford not to take it.

12
00:01:02,239 --> 00:01:05,730
Again, take your cue from the successful people.

13
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,409
Invest in yourself.

14
00:01:09,599 --> 00:01:11,170
Let's take action.

15
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:16,289
Now, in a quick recap, put these success-building principles to work.

16
00:01:16,289 --> 00:01:17,250
1.

17
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:20,050
Get a clear fix on where you want to go.

18
00:01:20,239 --> 00:01:23,250
Create an image of yourself 10 years from now.

19
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:24,210
2.

20
00:01:24,559 --> 00:01:26,690
Write out your 10-year plan.

21
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:29,809
Your life is too important to be left to chance.

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:36,289
Put down on paper what you want to accomplish in your work, your home, and your social departments.

23
00:01:36,879 --> 00:01:40,289
Three, surrender yourself to your desires.

24
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:42,690
Set goals to get more energy.

25
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:44,849
Set goals to get things done.

26
00:01:45,199 --> 00:01:49,090
Set goals and discover the real enjoyment of living.

27
00:01:49,839 --> 00:01:54,130
Four, let your major goal be your automatic pilot.

28
00:01:54,239 --> 00:02:00,210
When you let your goal absorb you, you'll find yourself making the right decisions to reach your goal.

29
00:02:01,119 --> 00:02:01,809
5.

30
00:02:02,079 --> 00:02:04,690
Achieve your goal one step at a time.

31
00:02:04,799 --> 00:02:11,490
Regard each task you perform, regardless of how small it may seem, as a step toward your goal.

32
00:02:11,490 --> 00:02:12,929
6.

33
00:02:13,279 --> 00:02:15,170
Build 30-day goals.

34
00:02:15,279 --> 00:02:17,650
Day-by-day effort pays off.

35
00:02:18,319 --> 00:02:19,010
7.

36
00:02:19,279 --> 00:02:21,409
Take detours in stride.

37
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:24,369
A detour simply means another route.

38
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:27,250
It should never mean surrendering the goal.

39
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:28,610
8.

40
00:02:28,879 --> 00:02:30,530
Invest in yourself.

41
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:34,690
Purchase those things that build mental power and efficiency.

42
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,530
Invest in education.

43
00:02:36,719 --> 00:02:39,570
Invest in idea starters.
